  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "PROJECT DIRECTOR",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Project Leadership & Delivery</strong></h3><ul><li>Lead and manage full-cycle construction projects from pre-construction to handover.</li><li>Develop and execute project strategies, schedules, budgets, and resource plans.</li><li>Monitor project progress, risk exposure, and performance metrics to ensure delivery targets are achieved.</li><li>Chair weekly project meetings with clients, consultants, subcontractors, and internal\n     teams.</li></ul><h3><strong>Contract & Commercial Management</strong></h3><ul><li>Oversee tendering, contract administration, VO/change control, procurement, and subcontract negotiations.</li><li>Monitor project cost plans, cash flow, and cost-to-complete forecasting.</li><li>Ensure compliance with contractual obligations, specifications, and statutory requirements.</li></ul><h3><strong>Technical & Construction Management</strong></h3><ul><li>Ensure construction methodologies, sequencing, and temporary works plans are technically sound and efficient.</li><li>Resolve technical and coordination issues in collaboration with consultants and construction teams.</li><li>Review and approve shop drawings, method statements, RA, FPP, QA/QC documents, and handover submissions.</li></ul><h3><strong>Safety, Quality & Regulatory Compliance</strong></h3><ul><li>Ensure compliance with Singapore regulations (e.g., BCA, SCDF,\nMOM, WSH Act).</li><li>Champion safety culture and ensure the implementation of WSH and\nQA/QC systems across all sites.</li><li>Oversee defect rectification and handover procedures.</li></ul><h3><strong>People & Team Development</strong></h3><ul><li>Lead and mentor project managers, engineers, QS, coordinators, and\nsite staff.</li></ul><ul><li>Conduct performance evaluations and develop training plans for\nproject teams.</li></ul><p><strong></strong><br /><strong>Education & Certification</strong>      \n</p><ul><li>Degree in Construction Management, Civil Engineering, Architecture, or related fields.</li><li>PMP, PE, or equivalent professional certifications are advantageous.</li></ul><h3><strong>Experience</strong></h3><ul><li>Minimum 10–15 years of relevant experience in the construction industry.</li><li>Proven track record in delivering commercial, residential, hospitality, or industrial projects.</li><li>Experience in managing multiple concurrent projects is preferred.</li></ul><h3><strong>Skills & Competencies</strong></h3><ul><li>Strong leadership, negotiation, and stakeholder management skills.</li><li>Proficient in cost control, contract administration, and procurement management.</li><li>Solid understanding of Singapore building codes, authority\nrequirements, and WSH regulations.</li><li>Ability to lead multidisciplinary teams and drive performance.</li><li>Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal.</li></ul>",
